### 7. Literature Review

| S.N. | Study | Findings (Key Points) |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| 1 | **Digital Nepal Framework** (GoN, 2019) | Emphasizes smart agriculture as a national priority and highlights the need for real-time agricultural data systems. |
| 2 | **Adoption of ICT in Agriculture** (FAO, 2021) | Early warning systems reduce crop losses by 30–40%, and mobile-based platforms significantly increase outreach in rural areas. |
| 3 | **Adoption of Digital Agriculture in Nepal** (Kathmandu University, 2022) | Farmers strongly prefer location-specific advisories over generic ones; trust in digital systems increases when recommendations are localized. |
| 4 | **AI in Agriculture Applications** (McKinsey & Company, 2023) | AI-based analytics improve crop monitoring and yield prediction; image-based disease detection effectively reduces dependency on manual experts. |

### 8. Expected Outcome

AgriSathi aims to create profound impact aligning with "Public-Private Collaboration for Effective Agriculture Commercialization."

*   **For Farmers:** Reduced crop losses through rapid AI disease detection; increased income through market intelligence; and improved resilience to climate shocks via localized early warnings.
*   **For the Government:** A shift from reactive to proactive governance; ability to plan interventions based on live, reliable data; and improved transparency in subsidy distribution.
*   **For the Province:** A robust agricultural value chain that minimizes waste, maximizes profit, and ensures food security through a data-driven approach.

